core.tut.pori.http.parameters

Class Limits

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.tut.pori.http.parameters.HTTPParameter
      • core.tut.pori.http.parameters.Limits

  • public final class Limits
extends HTTPParameter
    The default parser for limit parameters, the syntax being: ?limits=START_ITEM-END_ITEM with a possible open ended limit for END_ITEM, e.g. ?limits=START_ITEM in this case the END_ITEM is automatically assigned to START_ITEM+DEFAULT_MAX_ITEMS-1 It is also possible to provide limits for a specific type with ?limits=TYPE;START_ITEM-END_ITEM or for types with ?limits=TYPE;START_ITEM-END_ITEM,TYPE;START_ITEM-END_ITEM, the type limits can be retrieved using the parameterized getters, if no limits were provided for the type, default limits will be returned It is also possible to provide both the default limit and type specific limits: ?limits=START_ITEM-END_ITEM,TYPE;START_ITEM-END_ITEM Providing only the - character as a limit should as ?limits=- will be assumed to mean max items = 0, i.e. return nothing, this can also be used with typed limits, e.g. ?limits=0-1,TYPE;- to return no result for a specific type. The limits have no specific processing order, and can also be given in any order in the limits clause. The given order is generally internally preserved, though conceptually, no such order exists.
